Britain's Prince Harry and his wife Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, holding their son Archie, meet Archbishop Desmond Tutu at the Desmond & Leah Tutu Legacy Foundation in Cape Town, South Africa, September 25, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - There were squeals of delight and laughter when Archie met The Arch on Wednesday morning. Harry and Meghan, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex, took their young son to meet Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu in Cape Town. As they walked towards the meeting, a beaming Harry could be heard telling Archie, "You get to meet The Arch".  Once inside, video footage shows the royal couple speaking to a laughing Tutu, telling him that their son is getting used to having his photos taken and that he is an "old soul".